cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with training efficient deep neural networks for computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since the paper focuses on learning portable neural networks for computer vision. The second likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) since the paper proposes a novel framework for training efficient deep neural networks using generative adversarial networks. The third likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) since the paper deals with deep neural network compression and speed-up methods. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) since the paper proposes a method for training efficient neural networks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.MM (Multimedia) since the paper reports results on the CelebA benchmark, which is a face recognition dataset.
